                            <comment id="45283" author="chris" created="Thu, 20 Sep 2012 15:07:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When you say test-framework do you mean the test-infrastructure that is Autotest/Maloo/Toro or the test-framework that forms part of Lustre itself.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the later, which I suspect you mean, then it should be fixed as part of Lustre.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45257" author="hongchao.zhang" created="Thu, 20 Sep 2012 07:06:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this issue is caused by the failure of &quot;fail_loc&quot; reset,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;e.g.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/807ed662-0273-11e2-ab94-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/807ed662-0273-11e2-ab94-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in debug log,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test started at 1348039162&lt;br/&gt;
fail_loc set to OBD_FAIL_OST_BRW_WRITE_BULK at 1348039163&lt;br/&gt;
first ost_write failed for this fail_loc at 1348039168&lt;br/&gt;
fail_loc reset to 0 at 1348039173&lt;br/&gt;
last ost_write failed for this fail_loc at 1348039178&lt;br/&gt;
test failed at 1348039179&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but in console log, the fail_loc is reset at 1348039179&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;00:19:28:Lustre: DEBUG MARKER: lctl set_param fail_loc=0x20e&lt;br/&gt;
00:19:29:Lustre: *** cfs_fail_loc=20e, val=0***&lt;br/&gt;
00:19:40:Lustre: DEBUG MARKER: lctl set_param fail_loc=0&lt;br/&gt;
00:19:40:Lustre: DEBUG MARKER: /usr/sbin/lctl mark  sanity test_118i: @@@@@@ FAIL: got error, but should be not, rc=5 &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;is it related to the test framework?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
